**F002**
Severity: HIGH  
Category: code-bug  
Type: defect_fix  
Before-behavior: `check_new_module()` 以“缺 `MODULE.md`”近似“新模块”，任何被触碰但尚未补文档的存量模块都会进入 `missing` 并被 `block`。  
After-behavior: “新建模块” 与 “触碰存量模块” 必须分开判定，符合设计里的 `new -> block / legacy >=50 行 -> ask / 小改动 -> allow`。  
Evidence: [plan.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-plan.md:706)；[plan.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-plan.md:720)；[plan.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-plan.md:745)；[plan.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-plan.md:749)；[design.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-design.md:162)；[design.md](C:/Users/Administrator/edu-cloud/docs/plans/2026-04-13-module-governance-design.md:169)  
Impact: 一旦触碰现有未治理模块，hook 会提前硬阻断，直接违背设计声明的“渐进 ask、自愈式收敛”策略，误报率会非常高。  
Repair hypothesis (optional, non-authoritative): likely repair direction：先建立“模块是否新建”的独立证据源，再在 legacy 路径上应用行数阈值。forbidden fix patterns：通过降低阈值、全量放行、或继续把 `MODULE.md` 存在性当成新旧模块代理来掩盖误判。requires independent fix design + Semantic Regression Gate.

